      "content": "You can purchase a soil pH test kit from a garden store or online to determine the current pH level of your soil. Follow the instructions carefully to get an accurate reading. If the pH is too high (alkaline), adding sulfur or aluminum sulfate can help lower it. For too low (acidic) soil, you can add lime or wood ash to raise the pH. Remember to make adjustments gradually and retest the soil regularly to avoid shocking the plants' roots. Consulting a local gardening expert can also provide tailored advice for your specific situation.",
