      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If nitrogen deficiency is the issue, you might notice additional symptoms beyond yellowing leaves, such as stunted growth, purple or reddish leaves, or fewer and smaller leaves as the plant progresses. These signs are more indicative of a nutrient issue rather than a pest problem. However, if you do suspect a pest or disease, look for signs like holes in leaves, visible insects, or discolored spots that could indicate a fungus or insect infestation. Early detection and treatment are crucial to prevent further damage. Regularly inspecting your plants and maintaining good garden hygiene can help prevent many of these problems.",
      "source": "target",
